2. In this Ordinance, unless the context otherwise requires,-
[(a) “Director General” means the Director General of the Force;]
(b) “Force” means Special Security Force;
(c) “prescribed” means prescribed by rules made under this Ordinance;
(d) “very important person” means a head of state or Government of a foreign state and includes any other person who is declared by the Government, by notification in the official Gazette, to be such person for the purposes of this Ordinance.
